<p>All steps below are required to be done for each deployment</p><p>1. Take a backup of databases by using DbBackupMaster</p><p>2. Update Trello the information of the new release (version to be installed, date)</p><p>3. Start the installation with Jenkins and check until there is no issue</p><p>4. Test the application to be sure that it works fine</p><p>5. Copy the database backup files into revelent folders in&nbsp;AllApplicationReleases repository</p><p>6. Copy the new releases into&nbsp;AllApplicationReleases</p><p>7. Commit and Push the new files, to make sure that they are available in BitBucket.</p><p><br></p>